   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To convert the alarm signals sent from the system to EtherNet/IP
a AB9006 communication gateway is used. The AB9006 gateway converts
the Modbus TCP/IP signal sent from the network management card (NMC).</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The NMC card is required for using the AB9006 communication gateway.
The connection between the NMC and the AB9006 uses a straight Ethernet
cable (RJ45 connection).</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">A connection can then be made to the AB9006 gateway with a straight
Ethernet cable (RJ45 connection) to access the EtherNet/IP signals.</p>
